<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,504,691,750]" box="[151,439,726,750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,258,726,750]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,229,1982,2003]" captionTargetBox="[209,1375,175,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-60@43.[200,1382,158,1939]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 3. A–F. General habitus. (A) Gracilidia longiuscula, sp. nov.; (B) Gracilidia membrana, sp. nov.; (C) Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov.; (D) Coelidia angulata, sp. nov.; (E) Coelidia costaricensis, sp. nov.; (F) Dialodia brevilobata, sp. nov." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Plate 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[270,431,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs. 142–148</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,798,1614]" box="[151,694,798,823]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,799,823]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.50–8.00 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,798,1614]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,835,859]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Slender species. General color of dorsum dark brown to black with numerous yellow spots on veins of forewings, mesonotum, pronotum and crown, cells of forewings light brown, some with yellow spots; face black with numerous, small yellow markings (
<figureCitation box="[806,908,906,930]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,229,1982,2003]" captionTargetBox="[209,1375,175,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-60@43.[200,1382,158,1939]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 3. A–F. General habitus. (A) Gracilidia longiuscula, sp. nov.; (B) Gracilidia membrana, sp. nov.; (C) Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov.; (D) Coelidia angulata, sp. nov.; (E) Coelidia costaricensis, sp. nov.; (F) Dialodia brevilobata, sp. nov." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Plate 3B</figureCitation>
). Head significantly narrower than pronotum, anterior margin acutely angulate; crown narrow, about ¼ as wide as width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ of its entire length; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum about as long as median length of crown; mesonotum slightly longer than pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, broad at base, narrow at apex; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, very broad and inflated basally, lateral margins constricted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,798,1614]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,1086,1111]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with 2 caudal processes, caudodorsal process short, lobed, apex curved, caudoventral process long, very slender, membranous, nearly reaching base of caudodorsal lobe, small lenticular lobe basad of caudodorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[589,687,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 142</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, outer lateral margin expanded along distal 3/5 to 4/5, sparsely setose (
<figureCitation box="[587,684,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 143</figureCitation>
); style about as long as aedeagus, distal 3/5 very slender (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs. 144, 145</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, tubular, dorsal margin inflated submedially in lateral view, apex slightly swollen, armed with short narrow spine directed caudally (
<figureCitation box="[572,737,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs. 146, 147</figureCitation>
); connective small, Y-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1079,1176,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective not bifurcate basally, long, narrow, attached basally to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[984,1082,1302,1326]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–148" captionStartId="65.[151,257,1923,1944]" captionTargetBox="[228,1371,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-60@65.[208,1382,149,1929]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 142–148. Gracilidia tubercula, sp. nov. (142) male pygofer, lateral view; (143) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (144) right style, lateral view; (145) right style, dorsal view; (146) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (147) aedeagus, dorsal view; (148) connective, caudal view." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 146</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
